<LanguageData>
  
  <!-- EN: LingLong fruit -->
  <RI_Resource_LingLongFruit.label>玲珑珍果</RI_Resource_LingLongFruit.label>
  <!-- EN: Rarely is the Linglong Fruit found in this world, Enduring frost, wind, rain, and dew through countless trials.\nNot meant for mortal tongues craving sweetness, It is bestowed only upon those fated to tread the path of cultivation.\n\nA rare and precious fruit that requires many seasonal cycles to mature, yielding only a small harvest. When ripe, it is enclosed in a shell as hard as jade, which must be carefully opened to preserve the flesh within. The fruit is crisp and sweet, with a pear-like flavor that brings a gentle sense of comfort. Rich in spiritual energy, it nourishes qi and blood, making it particularly beneficial for those recovering from long-standing injuries. -->
  <RI_Resource_LingLongFruit.description>世间难遇玲珑果，霜风雨露几经沉。\n非为凡口贪甘美，只赠有缘修仙人。\n\n玲珑珍果为一种罕见的珍果，自果树萌芽，往往需历经数次季节轮转才能结出少量果实。成熟后，珍果外壳坚硬如玉，需要一些技巧，将果壳剥开，才能不损伤内部果肉。果肉甘甜脆爽，带有梨子风味，食之令人心生愉悦。玲珑珍果蕴含灵气，可滋养气血，对久伤未愈之人尤为适宜。</RI_Resource_LingLongFruit.description>
  
</LanguageData>